<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body 
of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<em>Title of Work</em>. Name(s) of Director(s). Name(s) of Performer(s). Publisher, 
	year of publication. Medium of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<em><span class="hover" class="hover" title="Title of Work">Outside the Lines</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) of Director(s)">Dir. Archie Smith</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) of Performer(s)">Perf. Carrie Chan, Darryn Williams, and Manu Tahatai</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Upbeat Pictures</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Medium of publication">Film</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are citing the contribution of a particular individual (here the director), begin with 
that person&#8217;s name.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Contributor&#8217;s name">Archie Smith, dir</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Work">Outside the Lines</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) of Director(s)">Perf. Carrie Chan, Darryn Williams, and Manu Tahatai</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) of Performer(s)">Upbeat Pictures</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">2056</span>. 
	<span title="year of publication">Film</span>.
</blockquote>
