<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
When a work is listed by title in the Works Cited, include in your text the title of the work 
(shortened if necessary), italicised within parentheses, immediately following the cited material.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;a sense of heightened emotion (<em>Outside the Lines</em>).
</blockquote>
<br>
Since page numbers cannot be given to direct your reader, when referring to a specific part of the 
film, describe the scene as accurately and concisely as possible.
